  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="19" style="v" />The way of the sluggard is like a thorn patch,</para>
  <para style="q2">but the path of the upright is a highway.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="20" style="v" />A wise son makes a father glad,</para>
  <para style="q2">but a foolish man despises his mother.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="21" style="v" />Folly is joy to one who is void of wisdom,</para>
  <para style="q2">but a man of understanding keeps his way straight.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="22" style="v" />Where there is no counsel, plans fail;</para>
  <para style="q2">but in a multitude of counsellors they are established.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="23" style="v" />Joy comes to a man with the reply of his mouth.</para>
  <para style="q2">How good is a word at the right time!</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="24" style="v" />The path of life leads upward for the wise,</para>
